{GREEN}Floor of the Valley{green}~
{BOLD}{GREEN}
   You examine your surroundings carefully, as you get a feeling that
   most everything around you is mage made.

   The lake is large and round, seeming to have formed by water
   draining into the bottom of the valley from the forest and
   mountains about it.

   It seems like centuries since you had a drink of fresh clean water,
   so you squat down to take a generous gulp. A force, not unlike a
   shield prevents you from even touching the crystal clear water.
   You jump back as electric tingles rush through your body. As you
   examine the body of mystical water more closely you see a scroll
   of some sort jutting from its sandy bottom. 

   Out of curiosity and bloody frustration, you sit helplessly on  the
   stump of an ancient oak, pondering the situation.
